## Student Management System Diagram

### Objective
Design a simple Student Management System module diagram.

### Description
The diagram illustrates the major modules of the Student Management System and their relationship with the central database.

### Modules
- Student Management
- Course Management
- Enrollment Management
- Attendance Management
- Grade Management
- Report Management
- User Management
- Database

### Diagram

![Student Management System](docs/student-management-system-diagram.png)

### Explanation
The Student Management System consists of seven main modules. Each module performs specific tasks such as managing students, courses, enrollment, attendance, grades, reports, and users. All modules are connected to a central database where the system stores and retrieves information.

### Learning Outcome
- Learned how to organize system modules.
- Understood the relationship between system components.
- Improved system analysis and documentation skills.
